Class AlphaZeroConfig

java.lang.Object
AI.alphazero.config.AlphaZeroConfig
public class AlphaZeroConfig extends Object
Configuration class for AlphaZero setup. Encapsulates all configuration parameters needed to set up an AlphaZero agent. Uses the builder pattern for flexible and readable configuration.

This class provides a centralized way to manage all AlphaZero hyperparameters and settings, including:

  • Board size
  • MCTS simulation count
  • Temperature for move selection
  • CPUCT exploration constant
  • Model file paths
  • Model loading preferences

Example usage: 

 AlphaZeroConfig config = new AlphaZeroConfig.Builder()
     .boardSize(7)
     .mctsIterations(200)
     .temperature(1.0)
     .cpuct(1.4)
     .modelPath("hex_alphazero_7x7.zip")
     .loadExistingModel(false)
     .build();

    • AlphaZeroConfig

      private AlphaZeroConfig(AlphaZeroConfig.Builder builder)
      Private constructor for builder pattern. Creates an immutable AlphaZeroConfig instance with parameters from the builder. This constructor is only accessible through the Builder class to enforce the builder pattern and ensure all configurations are properly validated.
      Parameters:
      builder - the builder containing validated configuration parameters

    • getTemperature

      public double getTemperature()
      Returns the temperature parameter for move selection. Temperature controls the randomness of move selection from the MCTS policy:
      • 0.0: Deterministic selection (always pick most-visited move)
      • 1.0: Stochastic selection proportional to visit counts
      Returns:
      the temperature value for move selection

    • getCpuct

      public double getCpuct()
      Returns the CPUCT (PUCT) exploration constant. This constant controls the exploration-exploitation tradeoff in the PUCT formula. Higher values encourage more exploration of less-visited moves.
      Returns:
      the CPUCT exploration constant

      public boolean isLoadExistingModel()
      Returns whether to load an existing model from disk or start with a fresh model.
      Returns:
      true if an existing model should be loaded, false to initialize a new model
